item.title: 龙卷风经过不来梅时，一家人在一个地下独立的预制掩体中避难
item.description:
Storm shelters are somewhat of a rarity in homes nowadays, but one family in Breman, Ky. said they wouldn't be here today if it wasn't for their shelter.
Jordan Evans and his son Gage were together when devastating storms and tornadoes hit western Kentucky late Friday night.
Gage was with his dad when the storm hit, but his mother and the rest of his family were right in the path of the storm. Their house didn't have a basement and there was no way to get below ground, except for one unique place just next door - a storm shelter, 10 feet down and 12 feet wide.
Read more: https://www.whas11.com/article/news/kentucky/storm-shelter-kentucky-tornadoes-bremen-saved/417-3c738abb-d953-4cd3-a077-051b8977bf59

The group can't get into any schools at all and it's clear that even though they didn't do anything wrong they've been cancelled.
Their lives are all ruined though and thus Peter goes to Doctor Strange in order erase this knowledge from everyone's mind so that his friends lives can have somewhat normality.

The movie picks up immediately after the events of Far From Home with Peter's identity out there and he has to live with the reprecussions of his new found fame. They even got some of the actors back from that scene including this guy who shows up in both films. Nice.
Though his name is cleared by none other than Matt Murdock his life and the life of his friends has been ruined by the court of public opinion and their applications to MIT are rejected. The group can't get into any schools at all and it's clear that even though they didn't do anything wrong they've been cancelled.
Their lives are all ruined though and thus Peter goes to Doctor Strange in order erase this knowledge from everyone's mind so that his friends lives can have somewhat normality.
